---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="First-Time China Travel Guide"
  description="A practical China travel hub for first-time visitors covering payment apps, internet access, hotels, addresses, transport, and itinerary planning."
  canonical="/china-travel/"
>
  <section class="content-page">
    <div class="hub-hero">
      <div class="page-header">
        <span class="eyebrow">First-time China travel</span>
        <h1>Plan a smoother first trip to China.</h1>
        <p>
          Focus on the practical details that affect every day of the trip: how you pay, how you get online, where you
          stay, how you show addresses, and how you move between places.
        </p>
        <div class="inline-actions">
          <a class="button" href="/tools/china-trip-checklist/">Open trip checklist</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/blog/china-travel-checklist-first-time-visitors/">Read travel guide</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hub-visual" aria-label="China travel preparation summary">
        <div class="hub-stat"><span class="icon-badge">1</span><div><strong>Payment</strong><p>Set up mobile payment before arrival.</p></div></div>
        <div class="hub-stat"><span class="icon-badge">2</span><div><strong>Address</strong><p>Save hotel details in Chinese.</p></div></div>
        <div class="hub-stat"><span class="icon-badge">3</span><div><strong>Route</strong><p>Plan metro, taxi, and daily areas.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="content-grid">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Who this guide is for</h2>
        <p>
          This guide is for first-time visitors who want a simple, reliable setup before arriving in China. It is useful
          for tourists, business travelers, trade fair visitors adding a few travel days, and anyone who feels unsure
          about payment, maps, transport, or hotel location.
        </p>

        <h2>Common problems first-time visitors run into</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>Arriving without a tested payment app or backup payment method</li>
          <li>Using a hotel address that drivers or map apps cannot easily recognize</li>
          <li>Choosing a hotel that looks central on a map but is inconvenient by metro</li>
          <li>Planning too many cross-city stops in one day</li>
          <li>Depending on English signs or English-speaking staff everywhere</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What to prepare before you travel</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>Install and test Alipay or WeChat Pay before departure</li>
          <li>Choose an eSIM, roaming plan, or local SIM option for internet access</li>
          <li>Save hotel names and addresses in Chinese, plus nearby landmarks</li>
          <li>Check metro access before booking hotels</li>
          <li>Group each day by neighborhood instead of crossing the city repeatedly</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Recommended guides and tools</h2>
        <div class="resource-grid">
          <a class="resource-card" href="/blog/china-travel-checklist-first-time-visitors/">
            <span class="card-kicker">Guide</span>
            <h3>China Travel Checklist</h3>
            <p>Payment, internet, addresses, transport, and realistic daily plans.</p>
            <strong>Read guide</strong>
          </a>
          <a class="resource-card" href="/tools/china-trip-checklist/">
            <span class="card-kicker">Tool</span>
            <h3>China Trip Checklist</h3>
            <p>A copyable pre-trip checklist for first-time visitors.</p>
            <strong>Open checklist</strong>
          </a>
          <a class="resource-card" href="/canton-fair/">
            <span class="card-kicker">Next path</span>
            <h3>Canton Fair Guide</h3>
            <p>Useful if your Guangzhou trip includes trade fair days.</p>
            <strong>Open hub</strong>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="sidebar">
        <div class="notice-box">
          <h2>Starter guide</h2>
          <p>Use the checklist to confirm payment, internet, hotel location, address, and transport basics before departure.</p>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/blog/china-travel-checklist-first-time-visitors/">Read checklist</a>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
